    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Electromagnetic Field: Point Charge\n\nThe electric field of a point charge is $\\mathbf{E} = -\\nabla V$ where $V = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{x^2+y^2}}$.\n\nWe add a small regularization term (0.1) to avoid the singularity at the origin, then let Maxima differentiate symbolically.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Point charge potential (regularized) */\nV_charge : 1/sqrt(x^2 + y^2 + 0.1)$\nEx : -diff(V_charge, x)$\nEy : -diff(V_charge, y)$\nprint(\"E =\", [Ex, Ey])$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 92,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "E = [x/(y^2+x^2+0.1)^(3/2),y/(y^2+x^2+0.1)^(3/2)]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Electric field radiates outward from the charge */\nax_draw2d(\n  normalize=true, name=\"E\", ngrid=12,\n  ax_vector_field(Ex, Ey, x, -3, 3, y, -3, 3),\n  title=\"Electric Field: Point Charge\",\n  aspect_ratio=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 93,
      "outputs": [
        {
